vel 10 troll warrior on Mith Marr and was wondering what you guys would recommend me trying to shoot for as far as armor/weapons goes.  I don't have access to any 'twinking' so have no way to start above my means.  I'm wearing a few pieces of netted armor atm and am wielding a fine steel piercer that someone just gave me yesterday.   Any ideas are most welcomed.  Thanks!<br>
<br>
Kravitz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 651<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 10:14:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4672.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: True newbie seeking advice on armor/weapons</span><hr size=1> My advice, farm spiderlings and spiders.  Get a couple of stacks of spiderling and spider silk and sell them in the bazaar for about 20pp a stack (1pp each).  Use the money to buy banded (a reasonable starter armor).  It may take a while, but there aren't many options when first starting out. <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=torqe>Torqe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 10:29:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4672.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: True newbie seeking advice on armor/weapons</span><hr size=1> Skeletons are decent for cash. Stacks of bonechips range from 5-20pp a stack and drop rusty weapons that sell for a few. I would suggest working on getting some Valdious Armor (sp?) if you got Luclin you can run to bazaar and find it for real cheap like 25-50pp a peice and they really good for price. i would save up and buy the bigger items like Breastplate and leggings them owrk on other items. Also i suggest getting some ghetto weapons in bazaar also i know some mighty fine weapon i use to use way back when that did very well run for about 10pp anymore so there is a good idea. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.fortunecity.com/orange99//sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dragonball477.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
