Summonist- 54 Mage<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azlanaicelander>Azlana Icelander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sexies Warlady in all o'Norrath</BR>     ...an da moon too!</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 519<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/02 12:17:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4672.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ringofshadows.org/images/Azlana7.jpg width=96 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: True newbie seeking advice on armor/weapons</span><hr size=1>  Found dis!<br>
<br>
Hergror is hungry, and he wants a Fungus Dung Pie (yech). He says to go to tell Carver Cagrek &quot;Hergror wants his Fungus Dung Pie&quot;.<br>
<br>
He is the troll on the dias in front of the Shaman's Guild near the bank. When you talk to Cagrek, he complains that Hergror is always hungry and that he needs 4 Fungus Spores to make a pie, but not to hit them too hard or you ruin them.<br>
<br>
The spores are dropped on a very rare occasion by fungus spores in Innothule. If you complete this and give Hergror the pie, he will award you with some patchwork, leather or raw-hide armor. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
