bronze 2 hand sword, so you can find some decent loot for your level. Once you get a couple of more levels, if you have the Luclin expansion, head to Paludal Caverns. The Recondite smugglers drop bronze armor pieces that you can either wear or sell to NPC vendors for 1-3 Platnium, and the experience there is the best in the game from 14-24. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnawbone>Gnawbone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/18/02 3:32:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4672.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ah the memories</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
If you are PoP enabled, I'd also recommend heading to Kurn's tower for cash. It's an excellent xp dungeon where you will get more than enough bone chips to keep your bank roll phat, especially if you are lucky enough to have a high level farmer in there looking for chips.<br>
<br>
Banded is a great value until you get to your 20s and when you can start affording crafted and crustacean, which will take you well into your 30s.<br>
<br>
Weapons are better if they are lower delay because you'll want to keep all your skills up in the early levels and you can go entire levels without maxing skills, especially with the horrible troll dexterity. Once you hit 20 though, look for weapons with good ratio more than anything else because your damage output won't capped as badly.<br>
